{"root":{"children":[{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Introduction","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"toc-heading","version":1,"tag":"h1","id":"introduction"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Welcome! ","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"toc-heading","version":1,"tag":"h2","id":"welcome!"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Hello! welcome to the step-by-step guide of making a full animation doing the best to mimic a professional workflow in open-source! Just a few notes before we start:","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"left","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1,"textFormat":0,"textStyle":""},{"children":[{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"This is an ","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"ALPHA","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":". So things are still a bit rough around the edges and continually being updated (hopefully you all can help with making it better!) ","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Not everything in this project is open-source there were two software I struggled replacing. Storyboard Pro (Which I will experiment replacing with blender after the 5.0 update that includes a dedicated Storyboarding workplace) and Davinci Resolve (While I used the free version of Davinci  for this entire process, it is not an open-source project. There are simply no great FOSS alternatives to Davinci's Fusion tab that I could find right now. ","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":2},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"I will ","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"NOT","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":" be talking about basic fundamentals so, no explanations on how to 2D animate, 3D model, digital painting etc. This guide is more about explaining niche features and interoperability between software.","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":3}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"list","version":1,"listType":"bullet","start":1,"tag":"ul"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Who's it for ","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"toc-heading","version":1,"tag":"h2","id":"who's-it-for"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"This is mostly appealing toward frame-by-frame animators who use 3D in their process, specifically for backgrounds and props. Full 3D animators probably won't find much use in this. 2D puppet animators mileage will vary as well as there are not really any FOSS alternatives for the 2D puppet animation workflow.","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1,"textFormat":0,"textStyle":""},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Alright let's get started!","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1,"textFormat":0,"textStyle":""}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"root","version":1}}